in wit, over ruling environmental mediocrity and daring for great and indelible change out of comfort or discomfort.', 4606, 0), (145067, 'Emergencies send sparks to the darkest corner of us. They wake up our hormones and neurotransmitters, they remove the rust from our body and mind, and they show us we can still handle crisis with poise. Emergencies push us to our limits. At those limits, the best inside us comes out. The eyes of our mind open, exceptional vision occurs to us, and we have a chance to become extraordinary.', 27279, 0), (145068, 'External conflicts we can avoid, resolve, or manage. But, when it comes to internal conflicts, there is only one viable option: resolve. Whatever internal conflict, major or minor, we don''t resolve will grate within us nonstop. Fortunately, we can resolve all our internal conflicts with one simple strategy: Act the way it feels right, no matter how inconvenient the consequences are.', 27279, 0), (145069, 'Not every wall needs a ceiling', 2760, 0), (145070, 'You are what you believe', 3682, 0), (145071, 'Experience is hard to acquire. Only the wise acquire it', 3682, 0), (145072, 'A good man can be destroyed by the association with men of evil character. A wise man can learn from them', 3682, 0), (145073, 'If there is no reward, there is no reason to run', 3682, 0), (145074, 'Know the laws before you break them', 3682, 0), (145075, 'Please others and you please yourself', 3682, 0), (145076, 'Calm is the best revenge', 3682, 0), (145077, 'Some people have the license to sin: Soldiers, to kill; politicians, writers, priests, businessmen, married man and women, to lie; and married couples to have sex', 3682, 0), (145078, 'You can have some, but not all. Wanting to have it all is a sure recipe for disaster', 3682, 0), (145079, 'Without roots a tree, no matter how tall, cannot stand.', 5104, 0), (145080, 'If you want an abscess to cure you must press it hard', 3682, 0), (145081, 'At the door is at the door. Beware, there are wolves.', 27280, 0), (145082, 'Turn your frowns into smiles, your tears into laughter, your weaknesses into strengths, your setbacks into opportunities, and your failures into victories.', 5104, 0), (145083, 'It''s always easy to conquer the hungry with a piece of bread. Only the wise can conquer the strong', 3682, 0), (145084, 'It''s not what we can do that makes us great, but what we can do but don''t which make us great', 3682, 0), (145085, 'Even if you are not evil, pretend to be. It will put off some abuse', 3682, 0), (145086, 'The hardest thing is a man to truly know himself', 3682, 0), (145087, 'Life is a sweet sour adventure. When you want to go it becomes sweet, when you remain, it becomes sour', 3682, 0), (145088, 'The problem with satisfaction is it''s a bottomless pit', 3682, 0), (145089, 'Forget about the great astounding victory. Focus on winning small victories every day, the final victory will come by itself', 3682, 0), (145090, 'You cannot skip the beginning and hope to reach the end. You will fall as soon as you get there', 3682, 0), (145091, 'The question is never ''who am I?'' It''s ''who do I want to be?', 6452, 0), (145092, 'If you allow coldness to engulf you before winter, season is helpless to help you.', 2760, 0), (145093, 'You seem irrelevant because your relevance seems latent. You seem irrelevant because your relevance is not speaking the language they understand. You seem irrelevant because you have not yet proven the evidence that is relevant. You seem irrelevant because you are still holding your relevance. People are more interested in works that work than mere works. People are much more interested in the relevance of actions than mere actions. People are more interested in your whole self in action and the relevance of the action than your mere action. There is something to be done. There is a footprint to leave. We must do something relevant. A proven relevance is relevant for our relevance in all matters of life.', 4606, 0), (145094, 'A good conscience is an epitome of good life and a true standard of living', 4606, 0), (145095, 'life is full of fantasies. Life is full of realities. Fantasies bring fantasies and realities bring realities. You have a choice. Yes, an inevasible choice. To live in the world of fantasies or to live in the world of realities; your choice!', 4606, 0), (145096, 'The greatest wisdom is to be happy', 3682, 0), (145097, 'You listen to people so that you can imagine them, and you hear all the terrible and wonderful things people do to themselves and to one another,but in the end the listenin EXPOSES you even more that in exposes the people you''re trying to listen to.', 9, 0), (145098, 'A little drop each day eventually fills the sea.', 5104, 0), (145099, 'Two hands cut down a few trees, but one matchstick clears a forest.', 5104, 0), (145100, 'Losing one feather does not prevent a bird from flying.', 5104, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (145101, 'The world of reality exists. The world of fantasy exists. The great boundary between the world of reality and the world of fantasy is the boundary of pleasure and fallacy. So many people enter into the world of realities through the the gate of betrayal and pain of the world of fantasies. If you live in the world of fantasies, ponder!If you live in the world of realities, learn and use your lessons.', 4606, 0), (145102, 'Water is not frightened of the ocean. Light is not frightened of the Sun.', 5104, 0), (145103, 'The sun that warms is also the sun that burns.', 5104, 0), (145104, 'You cannot cross large rivers without building bridges.', 5104, 0), (145105, 'He who hunts deer must not boast to he who hunts buffalo.', 5104, 0), (145106, 'Nurture a tree today, and it will provide you shade tomorrow.', 5104, 0), (145107, 'Only a fool lights a fire and tries to hide at the same time.', 5104, 0), (145108, 'Rain does not fall on one tree.', 5104, 0), (145109, 'Only when the lion is out of sight can you raise your fist at him.', 5104, 0), (145110, 'Small bait cast properly can catch big fish.', 5104, 0), (145111, 'The sea, no matter how endless, depends on rivers.', 5104, 0), (145112, 'Only the moon''s smile can cure the unseen scars of darkness', 2760, 0), (145113, 'It is a solemn duty to change lives positively.It is a noble honor to inspire and be there for others.It is an irresistible necessity to have empathy', 27281, 0), (145114, 'I don''t belong in this world, I am merely a traveller passing through, I repudiate to silence my thought, because they fear my light.', 3305, 0), (145115, 'Humanity is a very interesting phenomenon. If you peel back the layers, if you''re brave enough, you realize it''s something that''s not for the faint of heart-" Angel M.B. Chadwick', 27282, 0), (145116, 'Little is the imagination of the person who believes that the future of another may be determined by his/her past. We are so much more than our minds and our memories! We are in fact transcendent souls. If you determine what is ahead by what you can see when you look back, then you will in fact never behold what actually stands in front of you.', 103, 0), (145117, 'Life just happens, Alice. What makes us special is how we react to it.', 27283, 0), (145118, 'I think poetry without metaphor is like husband and wife living in separate bedrooms.', 2760, 0), (145119, 'we are bound to make mistakes. We are bound to meet mistakes. We have regretted certain decisions we took yesterday today and we may regret some decisions of today tomorrow but not until we regret the regrets, we shall always have the regrets', 4606, 0), (145120, 'Fish are small, but do not drown in the sea. Ships are big, but sink in the ocean.', 5104, 0), (145121, 'The best trees produce the sweetest fruits.', 5104, 0), (145122, 'To make dollars from cents you have to have sense.', 5104, 0), (145123, 'Strive to have the faith of a child', 27284, 0), (145124, 'Use your wisdom and life’s lessons to take you higher. Give yourself no other choices but to move forward and to succeed.', 19286, 0), (145125, 'Words can make or break, use your words carefully', 3682, 0), (145126, 'The ocean cries every time it loses a drop.', 27285, 0), (145127, 'Why fish in the pond when you live right next to the sea?', 5104, 0), (145128, 'The size of the seed does not determine the size of the tree.', 5104, 0), (145129, 'Comfort blindfolds; difficulty brings realization.Pain reveals; disappointments plant trigger of actions.Fear controls; ignorance deceives.Anger torments; silence keeps.Misunderstanding divides; love joins.Laughter starts; deception suspects.Frowning cautions; sorrow remembers.Purposefulness moves; idleness wastes.When you live in comfort, ponder.When you live in pain, take lessons.When life goes up, plant your feet and appreciate the height.When life goes down, envision the height and dare to get there with tenacity. Life is how you take and manage things. Be a manager of things or things shall be your manager', 4606, 0), (145130, 'In today''s time, no other ''''charity'''' is acceptable or practical than the ''''wisdom'''' that can transform the human life... Meaning the knowledge which can teach a man to climb the ladder of success.', 19454, 0), (145131, 'A predator on land is prey in the sea.', 5104, 0), (145132, 'Writing is Amazing!When I write I am empowered by my thoughts, entertained by my imagination, and enlightened by my wisdom.', 4539, 0), (145133, 'The shrewd help the strong.The wise help the weak.', 5104, 0), (145134, 'solemnly keep your deeds in silence', 27286, 0), (145135, 'When the wind blows, the weak are carried away by it, the strong resist it, and the wise manipulate it.', 5104, 0), (145136, 'Wisdom is a lamp', 27287, 0), (145137, 'How do you know if something is real? That’s easy. Does it change you? Does it form you? Does it give you wings? Does it give you roots? Does it make you look back at a month ago and say, “I am a whole different person right now”? If yes, then it’s real. The evidence of truth and reality, lies in how much something can touch you, can change you, even if it’s from very far away. Distance is only the evidence of what can be surpassed.', 103, 0), (145138, 'Power tends to corrupt, and absolute power corrupts absolutely. Great men are almost always bad men.', 2696, 0), (145139, 'Every girl and every woman, has the potential to make this world a better place, and that potential lies in the act of thinking higher thoughts and feeling deeper things. When women and girls, everywhere, begin to see themselves as more than inanimate objects; but as beautiful beings capable of deep feelings and high thoughts, this has the capacity to create change all around. The kind of change that is for the better. Remember: High in the head and deep in the heart. Antlers on your mind and anchors in your heart.', 103, 0), (145140, 'I have a dream, I have a vision, I have a mission, I have to do something, I will do this at this time; the thoughts of everybody; how do I deal with that obstacle? how do I get there? ; troubling questions for everybody! Releasing ourselves, plugging into the purpose, challenging the challenges, questioning the unquestionable, taking the chances; the asset and audacity of somebody. Everybody has a dream but, it is somebody who gets to the dream.', 4606, 0), (145141, 'I don''t always believe in God, but, I believe something is amiss.', 27282, 0), (145142, 'A lantern can give you light only when you light it', 2760, 0), (145143, 'If nobody in the world were to think that I am a good person; I wouldn''t care! I am aware of the fact that goodness does not materialise due to popular opinion! Goodness in fact is a state of the heart, and the heart is something that is only seen by those who have good enough eyes to see it. I am in fact more interested in being good; than in maintaining the appearance of goodness.', 103, 0), (145144, 'Misunderstandings are a normal part of life, and the outcomes of these depend upon how we choose to react to them.', 103, 0), (145145, 'Free your mind. Disentangle your mindset from what can set your mind from your true purpose. Dare when you have to. Enjoy when it is a must. Relax when there is the need to, but, don’t spend the time. Don’t let wealth be a hindrance to fulfilling your true you. Don’t let poverty captivate your true you. Don’t let the environment engulf your true purpose; if possible flee to be free to dare. We all have excuses. Yourself is the most important factor in fulfilling your true you. Free your mind!!!', 4606, 0), (145146, 'Absolute love, heals absolutely.', 27288, 0), (145147, 'To catch any fish, give it what it eats.', 5104, 0), (145148, 'The ball and chain of creativity has no key', 2538, 0), (145149, 'When something means nothing to you, you can do everything you want; but someday, somehow you may have to pay for it.', 2760, 0), (145150, 'The young have everything but wisdom.', 437, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (145151, 'FOOD FOR THOUGHT: Intelligent people speaks based on facts. Intelligent people speaks based on knowledge. Intelligent people don''t make a fool of themselves by assuming. Intelligent people seeks Truth. Intelligent people always seek hard facts when they are not sure. INTELLIGENT people don''t ridicule other people based on assumption. Intelligent people don''t generalise, the world is fill with over 7 billion people which is controlled by only 20% intellectual minded people (Pareto''s Law of 80/20) Only Shallow people speaks based on their narrow minds even when the TRUTH and facts are there for them to see, cos their small and narrow mind can''t connect to their brain since there is no link. Proverbs 4 vs 7 says Wisdom is the principal thing; therefore get wisdom: and with all your getting get understanding. Happy Sunday Folks', 27289, 0), (145152, 'Be as wise as a fox. Be as harmless as a dove.', 5104, 0), (145153, 'A mere love of wisdom is often enough to make oneself wiser.', 2892, 0), (145154, 'Our miseries are inseparable, so is our every single blessing.', 2760, 0), (145155, 'Happiness is a fantasy that real people know doesn''t exist.', 27282, 0), (145156, 'Solving a problem is intelligence. Preventing a problem is wisdom.', 5104, 0), (145157, 'Only those that make “Peace” shall have peace of mind. For in the creating of peace there is a solace of the heart and mind that surrenders logic for calm. A calm that only thosewho know how to be still within their mind can be open to many wondrous things. Peace for its own sake is empty. Peace when it is shared is truly lasting and harmonious.Surrender your havoc and know the healing fortitude that a gentle peace can only offer through unconditional love. Amen.', 27288, 0), (145158, 'One cannot truthfully profess a belief in a God, without having the ability to express the same sentiments towards other people around him/her. If you are going to say that you believe in a God that you cannot see, then you ought to believe in people that you can’t see, either! So much more faith and trust is required, to believe in an essence that you will never see with your own two eyes in this lifetime, than to believe in what you actually know can exist— other people. One must not be a hypocrite. During the times that I didn’t believe in people— I didn’t believe in God, either! During the times that I didn’t trust anyone— I didn’t trust God, either. The stuff of the soul, when it is genuine, will be reflected onto the way we think about, and interact with, other people! Don’t tell me you know a God who loves— if you don’t know how to love other people. Don’t tell me you have faith in a God, when you can’t have faith in another person. God is not there to show us that people can''t be trusted. God is there to show us Himself, in everyone and in everything.', 103, 0), (145159, 'If there is no room in the river,swim to the ocean.', 5104, 0), (145160, 'You win minds through your brilliance. You win hearts through your tenderness. You win souls through your benevolence.', 5104, 0), (145161, 'The mistakes of the wise lead them to light. The triumphs of fools lead them to darkness.', 5104, 0), (145162, 'challenges are everywhere. Awake! challenge and defeat the challenges that challenge you in a challenging way and be not be defeated by the challenges that challenge you in a challenging way', 4606, 0), (145163, 'Time appears to be most wasted when someone seeks truth in lies', 2760, 0), (145164, 'Many of the people in this world that you will see and that you will meet, are the versions of themselves that have come about as a result of the things that have happened to them in life. When people laugh at you, you develop a layer of skin for that and when you lose people, you develop a different layer of skin for that and when you are hurt during the times you are vulnerable, there is another special layer of skin for that; so on and so forth. We become covered in layers of different kinds of skin that we never asked to have and that we would never want to have! But there we are, underneath all of that; we walk around and we don''t see ourselves, we don''t see each other, we can hardly remember anything about who we are! It takes someone to look through all of that skin, to remember yourself on behalf of you. A person can give you the set of eyes that were used to view the real you, in some distant past, in some different lifetime! Then when you see them looking at you like that, you remember who you are and that''s when the layers of unwanted skin begin to peel and through that peeling you become a newborn.', 103, 0), (145165, 'Many people think that love represents chains, bondage, the opposite of freedom. But people who believe such things are simple-minded creatures who have been lied to, and who easily accept the general trend of the lie. It is in fact love that is the only thing powerful enough to set one free from even the most deeply-embedded and thoroughly-wound chains of the soul, the mind, and the body. The fact is that we are born into chains and born into bondages; these things are put upon us by fear, pain and doubt. When you are thoroughly loved by someone in mind and in heart, this has the power to set you so free, more free than you have ever been before. And that is because freedom is not the equivalent of detachment. Freedom is the equivalent of that which sets you free. And when someone loves you the way that only they can, that is what sets you free.', 103, 0), (145166, 'Sometimes I wonder why I exist with all my vast knowledge, while others exist longer with their clichés.', 27282, 0), (145167, 'notable people do notable things for they take notice of the unnoticed.They think beyond our thinking. They look beyond what we all look. They try, fail, and try again.They dare unrelentingly. They don''t die with their purpose. They die on their purpose. Though they die, their purpose ever lives.', 4606, 0), (145168, 'You cannot buy trust,you have to earn it.', 2760, 0), (145169, 'To be a climber one has to accept that gratification is rarely immediate.', 27290, 0), (145170, 'Pressure makes diamonds - or not.', 5164, 0), (145171, 'I think it is a wise person who does not answer the door to uninvited police officers. Who knows what kind of crazy person could be standing there with a loaded gun!', 5008, 0), (145172, 'the very day we get to know the enough is enough of our lives', 27291, 0), (145173, 'Stairs are your teacher; they teach you to be stronger. Love your teacher and every time life puts some stairs before you, accept them as a present!', 3701, 0), (145174, 'Follow both: the call of the mountain of enlightenment and the temptation of the valley of experience. No mountain without valley, no valley without mountain.', 5164, 0), (145175, 'It matters not what my brain knows, but what my heart feels.', 15319, 0), (145176, 'You may GIVE UP in self-denial but you GIVE–IN in denial of self.', 8543, 0), (145177, 'We are civilized animals doing uncivilized things.', 27282, 0), (145178, 'Prey cannot bribe its way out of a predator’s hand.', 5104, 0), (145179, 'Your spiritual brain is wisdom.', 19288, 0), (145180, 'Before knowledge comes understanding, before understanding comes wisdom.', 19288, 0), (145181, 'Have patience or be a patient. Have patience in preparatory moments or be a patient after preparatory moments', 4606, 0), (145182, 'To have a rich mind is better than to have a rich bank account.', 5104, 0), (145183, 'have patience or be a patient. Have patience in preparation moments or be a patient after preparation moments', 4606, 0), (145184, 'Light can only be understood with the wisdom of darkness.', 14393, 0), (145185, 'How can a falling dove turn again into a flying dove once again? It really takes the eyes of someone who sees you for the beauty that you really are. And if there are no other eyes there to see you in that way, then you had better be those pair of eyes, for yourself, to see yourself with!', 103, 0), (145186, 'Either way, it will cost you. You will for pay for your education or pay for your ignorance.', 11023, 0), (145187, 'Why a wise man is wise? The answer is simple: Because he has left his own shore!', 3701, 0), (145188, 'Humans naturally reflect their nature upon the nature of their God. So to know a person, just ask what the person thinks about their God. It’s either that, or an individual aims to reflect the nature of their God onto themselves; in either case, just ask about the God and you will know the person, or at least, what the person thinks of himself.', 103, 0), (145189, 'When you get wisdom, failure and discouragement will get behind you.', 3800, 0), (145190, 'Empathy isn’t about you, understanding another person isn’t about you, feeling how another person feels isn’t about you... step outside of your own skin for a change. Respect another person because they are who they are; not because the other person is just like you. Your inability to understand, your inability to empathize, is not a fault on the part of the other person. It is in fact your own disability that you are choosing to live with.', 103, 0), (145191, 'Try to get the important things right at all the time, even at the cost of being right.', 26490, 0), (145192, 'If you are a finger, your honesty is the hand to make your existence worth living.', 2760, 0), (145193, 'You see, it’s about empathy. It’s not about you. It’s about empathy. It’s not even about caring or being kind. It’s about empathy. Do you think that all people who can empathize with other people (and rocks and trees), are desirous of being kind, at all times? Of course not! Empathy often hurts, and is often difficult. But we experience this difficulty, because we are human beings, because human beings are designed to connect with other living and non-living things!', 103, 0), (145194, 'As we try to change society to fit our standards and bring about the sense of peace we long for, it is only when we turn inwards, clean our own backyards and serve as a source of inspiration that society will improve on its own.', 16372, 0), (145195, 'I believe that we are not determined either to heaven or to hell, through our actions here on Earth. On the contrary, I believe that we come either from heaven or from hell, prior to this life, and we carry our prior origins inside of us, at all times. People just go back to where they originally came from. And they live in this life as a result of where they once were. Of course, we have the capacities to develop and to build and to create more, while we are here, and perhaps even to change the course of our destinies, but I believe that the soul matter of individuals, are varied and are not of all the same origins.', 103, 0), (145196, 'Perhaps a human simply falls back into himself upon the disintegration of his physical body, and continues to take form within the self of himself, simply returning from whence he came.', 103, 0), (145197, 'Wisdom justifies a person in the face of any opposition', 3800, 0), (145198, 'If a person has wisdom, then he will also have the anointing. But sometimes a person with theanointing may not have much wisdom.', 3800, 0), (145199, 'The future of the Church is in the hands of wisdom', 3800, 0), (145200, 'In order to reach his destiny and have dominion over the earth, man has to get wisdom.', 3800, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (145201, 'Wisdom dwells in the heart of God.', 3800, 0), (145202, 'The first step towards obtaining wisdom is to acknowledge the sovereignty and authority of God and to be subject wholly to His will.', 3800, 0), (145203, 'The more the Word of God abides in a person, the more strength and wisdom he will have.', 3800, 0), (145204, 'Without wisdom man’s position does not differ in any way from that of a servant.', 3800, 0), (145205, 'A gentle and a sweet, innocent soul can come from any place, any background. It is the nature of the soul and it cannot really change on the inside. A soul like this may come to believe the tauntings of the circumstances in life, and of the people who created those circumstances, with only memories of the true reflection of who it (the soul) really is. The downfall begins when a beautiful soul starts to believe that it is not beautiful.', 103, 0), (145206, 'The most important thing in life is wisdom and not money', 3800, 0), (145207, 'Today is tomorrow’s stepping stone, but for the wise it is a ladder.', 5104, 0), (145208, 'Do today what will profit you tomorrow. Avoid forever what did not profit you yesterday.', 24104, 0), (145209, 'The simple act of being completely attentive & present to another person is an act of love, and it fosters unshakeable well-being.', 124, 0), (145210, 'The best source of information to use as frequently as possible......is your own bullshit meter.', 16372, 0), (145211, 'Be happy but when sad times come, know that God allow these time for self-realisation.', 2878, 0), (145212, 'I think that a lot of the time, people are generous towards those whom they pity; but only find fault in those whom they see as better than themselves. There is a fake kind of goodness; and that is the goodness that is only good towards other people that make the givers feel better about themselves. Would you be good to someone you think is so much better than you are? Or who has so much more than you have? Or is your goodness only reserved for those who make you feel like a god because you give to them? Too often, there are shining, beautiful people, who suffer so much in this world, because there would be so many others willing to snuff out their flames! Goodness of a person is not measured by sympathy or compassion; rather, goodness is measured by empathy. Empathy goes beyond all the physical things you see with your two eyes. It’s easy to be good to those you pity; much harder to be good to those whom you envy!', 103, 0), (145213, 'All times are sacred and must be kept Holy', 2878, 0), (145214, 'Everyone has something to think about everyday, but it is not everyone who thinks about something everyday. And that is the difference', 4606, 0), (145215, 'What you have in hand may be of less essence to knowing and using what you have in hand', 4606, 0), (145216, 'The spirit of volunteerism is the spirit of service.', 2878, 0), (145217, 'How many people actually read the Bible and follow it? The truth is right there. How many people know what a marriage or family is all about? Everything starts with an idea, but getting people to act is different. You can''t do something well if you don''t know what it is or tried it for awhile.', 5405, 0), (145218, 'Never assume you know it all. Ask questions.', 2878, 0), (145219, 'Always make time to eat. Always. There’s enough starving children in the world without adding to their number', 24567, 0), (145220, 'Each day is filled with beautiful splendid.', 2878, 0), (145221, 'Motivation ignites a flame of fire within our spirit.', 2878, 0), (145222, 'We have to be extremely careful in the manner which we live life.', 2878, 0), (145223, 'All times are determined by God.', 2878, 0), (145224, 'We cannot totally understand God but we can totally love God. Embrace God.', 24289, 0), (145225, 'Kindness beautifies your words.Love sweetens your words.Wisdom empowers your words.', 5104, 0), (145226, 'This moment is our greatest treasure. We cannot replay the past events. We have no control over future events.', 2878, 0), (145227, 'In the moment of decision, may you hear the voice of the Creator saying, ‘This is right road, travel on it.', 2878, 0), (145228, 'You can''t put your heart into everything; you''ve just got to show up. And if your heart is worn all over you, then so be it, but you can''t pull it out of you and put it in places, or put it in people''s hands. Because you are like this wild and quiet and laughing thing and people are like things that stand there and don''t understand what''s going on; so when you put your heart into things like that, you''re going to feel either stupid, or very hurt, or both. And it''s not people''s faults that they are just standing there. I mean, you''re the different one; they''re not different; they''re all the same.', 103, 0), (145229, 'It is the simple things that are in the ocean. People think that simple things are on the seashore, like seashells. But seashells are just illusions of the things that once used to live inside of them, that are back in the sea! They are dead things, and dead things are not simple things. Living things are simple things, things like love. People think that love isn''t simple, but that''s because they are on the seashore; but when you are a mermaid, when you have gills, when you need to be in the ocean; love is simple. It''s about being beside someone and staying there. And then sharing your souls. What''s natural to a mermaid, isn''t natural to a person. But I want everyone to be a mermaid. And if they can''t, at least they can know what a mermaid is like. We live with the things that are alive.', 103, 0), (145230, 'The power of writing supernaturally set things into motion.', 2878, 0), (145231, 'I am afraid of those who are too simple on the outside', 27292, 0), (145232, 'Keep on exploring.Keep on evolving.Keep on experimenting.', 2878, 0), (145233, 'Overcome darkness, so that you may walk in the light.', 2878, 0), (145234, 'Working together for a great mission is very fulfilling!', 2878, 0), (145235, 'The uniqueness of different colours represents the uniqueness of individuals!', 2878, 0), (145236, 'Great God of wonders', 27293, 0), (145237, 'Keep on questioning. Keep on searching.', 2878, 0), (145238, 'A wise servant is better than a foolish ruler.', 5104, 0), (145239, 'Walk with the Creator on the face of earth.', 2878, 0), (145240, 'To have an empty head is worse than to have an empty bank account.', 5104, 0), (145241, 'The eloquence of the pen is just as sharp as the point of a sword.', 5104, 0), (145242, 'The Lord is supreme.The Lord is strong.', 2878, 0), (145243, 'The dawn of light is the liberation of souls.', 2878, 0), (145244, 'Life''s a one way ticket', 4987, 0), (145245, 'It is a very strange thing to see so many images in the world around us... we don''t realise it, but we are all impressionable beings, able to pick up off of the images that bombard us on a daily basis. We are created and moulded by images and impressions. One of the most difficult tasks in life, is to keep a steady impression of something in your sight, and to believe in it until it becomes you. Because there is just so much temptation/opportunity, to become something else.', 103, 0), (145246, 'People who seek the truth never stop looking for it', 5405, 0), (145247, 'Believe in supernatural power.', 2878, 0), (145248, 'Living in harmony with one another brings inner tranquility', 2878, 0), (145249, 'It is easy to give up than to endure. Always choose the latter.', 2878, 0), (145250, 'All people want to belong to some sort of hierarchy. Allow me to explain. The rich want to be the richest; the poor want to be the smartest; those who are both rich and smart want to be the better persons; the better persons want to go to heaven; those who are in heaven will look down upon those who are in hell... there is always some kind of hierarchy desired by everyone; even by those who claim the opposite of this. So how do you find true divinity? Divinity is found in those who reach down low; because it is those who are above who must reach down low, while it is those who are below who must constantly reach for what is above! And this is divinity. What is divine, is what will have a curiosity in what is below. There is no fear of becoming "tainted"; because what is lesser can never really taint what is greater. it is what is greater than is able to transform what is lesser. The alchemist must first find the mud, pick it up, before she is able to transform it into diamond.', 103, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (145251, 'No one can successfully tell me that material things cannot bring happiness. For as the spirit is medicine to the bones; so is the happiness of the bones a medicine to the spirit. Without a soul, the body is dust; but without a body, the soul cannot fulfil destiny. Neither one is more important than the other; both are equally important. One will last longer than the other, yes, but while we are on this Earth, both are equally important. Surely money itself cannot make one happy; but it is what one does with money that makes one happy! If you do not know what to do with it, then it will not bring you happiness! But if you know what to do with it; there is no reason why it cannot bring you happiness. People think I am a very spiritual person; yes, this is true; but I have not achieved it through denial of the flesh. I have a new vision. I take pleasure in the pleasures of this world and I seek fulfilment in the answers of the spirit. I find happiness in the material and the physical things of this nature and I find joy in the connections I have with what is divine. Do I imagine myself on top of a mountain, detached from all the things I want to buy and to own? Never. My spirituality is not one of negative righteousness; my spirituality is one of the rose. It is whole and it is above as it is below.', 103, 0), (145252, 'The failure of the nation lies in the failure of its citizens.', 2878, 0), (145253, 'Knowledge is life. The more informed you are, the better you are in making the best decision.', 2878, 0), (145254, 'God determines the path of every man.', 2878, 0), (145255, 'A joyful soul, a grateful spirit full of love and light!', 2878, 0), (145256, 'Great places, great memories.', 2878, 0), (145257, 'It is a duty of every citizen to pray for those who are authority and the nation', 27294, 0), (145258, 'You shall not be afraid of the adversary. God will be your strong fortress.', 2878, 0), (145259, 'Our greatest quest in life should be to live in the light!', 2878, 0), (145260, 'Every nation must have prayerful men and women to intercede for the country’s well-being.', 2878, 0), (145261, 'Wisdom in poverty is better than folly in affluence.', 5104, 0), (145262, 'Path of life, path of light!', 2878, 0), (145263, 'We are all vessels of good honour.', 2878, 0), (145264, 'Results speak for themselves while intentions often fall short of promises.', 27295, 0), (145265, 'All men are guilty of the wrong they have done.', 2878, 0), (145266, 'Love thy soul, manifest thy light', 2878, 0), (145267, 'Never seek to please anyone. Seek to evolve thyself.', 2878, 0), (145268, 'We wait expectantly for what we hope for.', 2878, 0), (145269, 'You need to make effort and commit time to do what you love.', 2878, 0), (145270, 'You can survive the storm. Your soul is stronger than the storm.', 2878, 0), (145271, 'May you find the right path to your destination.', 2878, 0), (145272, 'Any training is initially difficult, but with persistence practice, we can master the art.', 2878, 0), (145273, 'You can capable of heroic deeds. Think well of yourself and act positively.', 2878, 0), (145274, 'The only limit to the realisation of our goals will be lack of enthusiasm.', 2878, 0), (145275, 'Hold on to hope and positive thoughts', 27296, 0), (145276, 'When you travel, be fully present in the place of voyage.', 2878, 0), (145277, 'The pursuit of dreams is supernatural endeavours.', 2878, 0), (145278, 'Wisdom is the ability to take two opposite facts and make sense from both of the them', 27297, 0), (145279, 'You can be critical and not judgmental. The two are synonyms, but not the same. The critical man analyzes people, things, and issues, very carefully. The judgmental man presents the results of his careful analysis in a manner that condemns.', 27298, 0), (145280, 'You can be critical and not judgmental. The two are synonyms, but no the same. The critical man analyzes people, things, and issues, very carefully. The judgmental man presents the results of his careful analysis in a manner that condemns.', 27299, 0), (145281, 'Find your passion and live it!', 2878, 0), (145282, 'I see any difficulty as an adventure.', 2878, 0), (145283, 'To be wise for one day is better than to be intelligent for a hundred.', 5104, 0), (145284, 'The pursuit of our dreams is not without any difficulty. Those who triumph have learn’t to overcome the difficulty.', 2878, 0), (145285, 'The greater your wisdom, the shorter the distance to success.', 5104, 0), (145286, 'You have great talents. Aim for God best for your life.', 2878, 0), (145287, 'We must be conscious of this; one day, the life we have, will be gone.', 2878, 0), (145288, 'Perhaps we are all shells; but some of us have found the pearls inside, and this makes all the difference!', 103, 0), (145289, 'If you have few days to live your life, what will be your passion for last days?', 2878, 0), (145290, 'The love of your life, is not the person who traps you into themselves; but the love of your life, is the person who sets you free from so many of the traps that you are already in! The love of your life, is not the person who blinds you to everyone else; but the love of your life, is the person who removes the many blindfolds that have accumulated on you, in your life. The lover for you, is the one who sets you free into themselves. You are freed from bondages, and inside of that freedom, stands that person! THAT is the lover for you!', 103, 0), (145291, 'The birth of a child is a sacred phenomenon.', 2878, 0), (145292, 'Thought is uncontrollable but controllable. Thought is the pivot of life and the epitome of good or bad living. A controlled thought is a controlled life and an uncontrolled life is an uncontrolled living. Our first and last thoughts from dawn to dusk are of great essence to living a purposeful life. They form a catalyst for a progressive or retrogressive life. What do you think of most before you